<h2><a name="vscanf_vfscanf_and_vsscanf" id="vscanf_vfscanf_and_vsscanf">vscanf, vfscanf and vsscanf</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>

Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdarg&gt;</span>
    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdio&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> vscanf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>format<span class="sy0">,</span> va_list arg_ptr <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    <span class="kw4">int</span> vfscanf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> FILE <span class="sy0">*</span>stream<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="kw4">const</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>format<span class="sy0">,</span> va_list arg_ptr <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    <span class="kw4">int</span> vsscanf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>buffer<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>format<span class="sy0">,</span> va_list arg_ptr <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>

These functions are very much like scanf(), fscanf(), and sscanf(). The
difference is that the argument list is a pointer to a list of arguments.
va_list is defined in cstdarg, and is also used by <a href="../other/va_arg" class="wikilink1" title="c:other:va_arg">va_arg</a>. For example:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     <span class="kw4">int</span> scanf_<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>fmt<span class="sy0">,</span> ... <span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
       va_list args;
       va_start<span class="br0">&#40;</span> args<span class="sy0">,</span> fmt <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
       <span class="kw4">int</span> r <span class="sy0">=</span> vscanf<span class="br0">&#40;</span>frmt<span class="sy0">,</span> args<span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
       scanf<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="st0">&quot;%*[^<span class="es0">\n</span>]&quot;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">,</span> getchar<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span>; <span class="co1">//Empty buffer</span>
       va_end<span class="br0">&#40;</span> args <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
       <span class="kw1">return</span> r;
     <span class="br0">&#125;</span></pre>
</div>
